Fights for civil rights in cyberspace, and co-founded by John Perry Barlow. 


=Description=

Wikipedia profile at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electronic_Frontier_Foundation

'''Extensive profile''' by MSNBC, at http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/13718446/

Excerpt: "The EFF continues to tackle issues like anonymity, electronic voting, patents and copyright, but the Sept. 11 attacks nearly five years ago have forced the EFF to spend more time on surveillance. It has sought to require more evidence before law enforcement can legally track people's locations by their cell phones, and in January the group sued AT&T, saying the San Antonio-based company violated U.S. law and the privacy of its customers. AT&T and NSA officials declined comment for this article."


